<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kalef Bonemender</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Im just curious, when you guys do a Ch rotation, what is the average amt you CH the MT with?  Im assuming you have others spot healing the MT to make sure the Ch lands? <P> Also, how can you avoid getting aggro with that first CH?  My guild rarely does a CH chain as we only have a few clerics and we arent very large, but we do some fights where im relegated to chain cast the spell, and i sometimes get aggro if i land a nice heal the first time.  Thanks for your help in advance!<P>Kalef Bonemender<BR>58 Cleric<BR>Quellious</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serina Moonprism Elay</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The amount of clerics that you use greatly depends on who you are fighting. There are times when my guild uses only 5 clerics and there are times we use 10.<P>As for early argo haveing an each cast +argo on the MT helps. Also if the mob is rooted in place the warrior can shoot some arrows at him to get the mob mad at the MT. <P>But sometimes that dosn't work. If your the first cleric to heal always be ready to cast DA or DB. Those can be life savers in a big battle.<P>Also, there are a few mobs that we do two rounds of DL at really fast intervals before switching over to CH's. This can reduce argo and give the MT a chance to get argo.<P>------------------<BR><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26064" TARGET=_blank>Serina Moonprism Elay</A></B><BR>60th High Priestess<BR><A HREF="http://www.prophecyguild.com" TARGET=_blank>Prophecy Guild</A> <BR>Member of the Elay Brotherhood<BR>Bertoxx Server<BR><I>"Be kind for everyone you meet is fighting a harder battle."</I>-Plato <BR><I>"Insanity is the root of all genius."</I> -Jen Meyskens</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Borick</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The number of clerics and the timing on the CH rotation varies from mob to mob.  On most mobs (TOV dragons) my guild uses a four-cleric, four-second rotation. For Avatar of War (The most difficult mob my guild kills at present) we use 10-12 clerics on a two-second rotation.<P>The actual amount that the clerics heal with each CH varies.  Verant has added a lot of randomness to how mobs do damage, just to limit the effectiveness of CH and rotations.  Flurries, rampages and the ability of a mob to hit in a random pattern within it's attack round all mean that clerics have to worry not about being mana efficient, but in making sure that we always heal within the maximum range of damage the mob can hit for. The irony of these changes is that it only reinforces the reliance of raids on Complete Heal even further.<P>For example, if Ubermob X 'normally' hits for 1k per second, but can flurry for an additional 4k once every 12 seconds, then every cleric in the rotation must assume an additional 4k of damage on his turn.  This means that many of the heals will be less efficient mana-wise than a Divine Light or Natures Touch would be, but it has to be that way or you couldn't take down these mobs.  On these mobs smaller heals couldn't compensate for the sudden spikes in damage output.<P>Also note that in order to maintain the longer rotations you're going to need an infastructure for the rotation.  For AOW you will need mages to cast plenty of three-charge mod rods.  Every melee will pick up a mod rod to drop during the fight.  Clerics will use the mod rods to replace mana during the fight, and druids/shamans have the task of keeping the clerics healed.  With practice you can maintain a rotation on any mob almost infinately.  Verant doesn't like it, but that's the only option they give us.  The developers have this unrealistic notion of using mass numbers to kill these mobs rather than 'exploiting' by using strict DPS and cleric rotations, but there's a point of diminishing returns with the 'zerg' method at which the raid lag actually reduces your ability to kill the mob.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viscera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What we do is have the patch healers (druids, shamans, paladins) spam heal the MA for a few seconds until we start the CHC. Midway through the CHC, we call the patch healers off to do their normal raid things.<P>Hardly ever have a problem with the first cleric getting aggro, though it still happens occasionally. Like Serina said, have DA ready just in case.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=191031" TARGET=_blank>Viscera Galen</A><BR>L60 High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://www.darktemplarsguild.co.uk" TARGET=_blank>Dark Templars</A><BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bindol</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Let me also mention keeping DA handy and using it if necessary.<P>My first time in a CH chain, I was first cleric.  The cleric running the chain had told me where to stand and when to start my heal.  I started casting exactly when the cleric told me to, and the CH hit when the tank was about a half bubble of life left.  <P>The mob then turned on me, and I hesitated on hitting DA.  The hesitation meant I listenned to the rest of the fight from the bazaar.<P>I didn't really mind dying, as it happens occasionally when you are a cleric.  The worst part was worrying that I had screwed up the entire encounter as the mob ran into the clerics to kill me, and we weren't that far from the casters.<P>Luckily everything else went fine, and I turned out to be the only death in fight.<P><P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105543" TARGET=_blank>Bindol Stonehealer</A> <BR>(Sol Ro)</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
